Parser generation here is taken to be the construction of LR(0) tables (i.e. , without any lookahead) for a particular TAG z. The moves made by the parser can be explained by an automaton which is weakly equivalent to TAGs called Bottom-Up Embedded Pushdown Automata (BEPDA) (Schabes and Vijay-Shanker, 1990) 3. 
